@startuml
title BP-25 - Payment Gateway Callback Processing

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  DiamondBackgroundColor White
  DiamondBorderColor Black
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
}

|Payment Gateway|
start
:Send payment callback;

|Platform|
:Verify callback signature;
:Find payment order by reference number;
:Check idempotency key or current status;

if (Callback already processed?) then (Yes)
  :Return success without duplicate changes;
  stop
else (No)
  :Continue processing;
endif

if (Payment successful?) then (Yes)
  :Mark payment order as COMPLETED;
  :Allocate payment to obligations if not already allocated;
  :Post ledger entries;
else (No)
  :Mark payment as FAILED or keep pending according to provider status;
endif

:Record callback audit trail;
:Prepare notification event;
stop

note right
Callback processing is future gateway scope.
Current MVP uses allocation flow to complete payment orders.
end note
@enduml
